{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[Bm]  I keep looking for something I can't get
[Gmaj7]     Broken hearts lie all around me
And I[A] don't see an easy way to get out[F#m7]    of this
Her [Bm]diary, it sits by the bedside table
The [Gmaj7]curtains are closed, the cats in the cradle
Who[A] would've thought that a boy like me could [F#m7]come to this
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
Oh [Bm]I, I just died[Em]  in your [Emadd9]arms  tonight[Aadd9][A]
It [F#m]must have been something you sa[Bm]id
I just died[Em]  in your [Emadd9]arms  tonight[A]
[F#m]   Oh [Bm]I, I just died[Em]  in your [Emadd9]arms  tonight[A]
[F#m]It must've been some kind of kiss[Bm]
I should've[Em]  walked away,[A]  [F#m]   I should've walked away[Gmaj7]
{end_of_chorus}


{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[Bm]  Is there [Bm]any just cause for feeling like this?
[Gmaj7]     On the surface, I'm a name on a list
I try[A] to be discreet, but then [F#m]blow it again
I've lost[Bm]  and found, it's my final mistake
She's [Gmaj7]loving by proxy, no give and all take
Cause I've[A] been thrilled to fantasy one too many[F#m]   times
{end_of_verse}


